    • getBaseName

      protected String getBaseName()
      Description copied from class: ClassGenerator
      Retrieves the base name of the class to be generated.

      This should be the simple name describing the class that is to be generated.

      For example, the base name of the generated EntityFallingBlock class would be just that: "EntityFallingBlock". Any additional information (such as the fact that it is a generated class) will be added later on by ClassGenerator.getFormattedName().

      Specified by:
      getBaseName in class ClassGenerator
      Returns:
      The base name of the class to be generated.
